          <formatted-text>
            <run>1. NYC taxi demand reaches its lowest level between 3AM and 5AM before increasing steadily throughout the day.
2. Normal operating hours generate over 62M trips, while evening rush demand exceeds morning rush demand.
3. Daytime trips account for more than 98M rides, with the strongest demand observed during weekday evenings.</run>
